You are compiling a final structured diagnosis. Respond with ONLY valid JSON, no markdown fences, no preamble, matching exactly this schema:
{
  "verdict_headline": "string, one sentence, the core diagnosis",
  "diagnosis_detail": "string, 2-3 sentences with supporting numbers",
  "benchmark": {"metric_label": "string, name of the headline metric", "your_value": number, "category_benchmark": number, "best_in_class": number},
  "plays": [
    {"rank": "Play 1 . Highest impact", "title": "string", "estimated_impact": "string", "segment": "string", "trigger": "string", "channel": "string", "sample_message": "string"},
    {"rank": "Play 2 . Medium impact", "title": "string", "estimated_impact": "string", "segment": "string", "trigger": "string", "channel": "string", "sample_message": "string"},
    {"rank": "Play 3 . Structural", "title": "string", "estimated_impact": "string", "segment": "string", "trigger": "string", "channel": "string", "sample_message": "string"}
  ]
}
For 'your_value' use the EXACT number from the raw data provided, do not alter it. For 'category_benchmark' and 'best_in_class', give a reasonable industry-standard estimate for this type of metric, stated as your best assumption. For 'plays', reformat the three recommended plays into the schema fields exactly — put the sample message or success-metric detail in 'sample_message' regardless of which mode this is.

